"""
Expected PostgreSQL reference rows for the small TPC-H fixture and comparison
helpers for YDB integration tests.

Oracle source: PostgreSQL 15 with create_postgres.sql / insert_postgres.sql.
Generated by running queries_postgres.sql against the fixture dataset.

None means the query has a known transpilation bug and is marked xfail.

Known xfails and their root causes:
  Q02 — correlated scalar subquery: decorrelate() loses outer-table reference
          after unnesting (same table names in inner and outer scope confuse scope
          resolution, causing the outer p_partkey column to be detached).
  Q04 — EXISTS subquery: not yet supported in decorrelate().
  Q11 — HAVING scalar subquery: decorrelate() incorrectly treats the non-correlated
          inner subquery as correlated because inner/outer queries share the same
          table names without aliases; incorrect GROUP BY is injected.
  Q13 — LEFT OUTER JOIN ON with unqualified columns: YDB requires table-qualified
          columns in JOIN ON clauses ("correlation name"), but the original SQL has
          none and schema info is needed to add them automatically.
  Q16 — COUNT(DISTINCT col) in JOIN query: YDB requires table-qualified columns
          in DISTINCT aggregates when there are JOINs.
  Q17 — correlated scalar subquery (0.2 * avg(l_quantity)) whose result column is
          auto-named "0.5" by the optimizer, breaking the HAVING reference.
  Q18 — l_orderkey is ambiguous after unnesting the IN subquery (appears in both
          the outer lineitem table and the unnested _u_0 alias).
  Q20 — same 0.5 * SUM() column-naming issue as Q17.
  Q21 — EXISTS / NOT EXISTS subqueries: not yet fully supported.
  Q22 — NOT EXISTS subquery: not yet supported.
"""

